														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-4652801">
									

<p>I'm not usually fond of Thaumatology, since having pure magic is usually detrimental to the more &quot;unknowable&quot; part of anomalies, but I find this to be the exception. The most we see of Thaumatology is not the focus of the article, and the dialogue with the &quot;hundred chains to bind me&quot; figure is great. Overall, the worldbuilding feels consistent, and the characters are powerful enough to make a compelling narrative. +1!</p>

							</div>

								
					
